---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import DocsSidebar from "../../components/DocsSidebar.astro";
---
<Layout
	title="Chrome extension · flipagent docs"
	description="The flipagent Chrome extension scores eBay listings on the page itself and lets your agent place orders inside your own browser."
>
	<div class="cmw cmw-bordered">
		<div class="docs-shell">
			<DocsSidebar />
			<article class="docs-content">
				<h1>Chrome extension</h1>
				<p class="lead">Two things in one extension. While you browse eBay, it scores every listing right on the page. While your agent works, it opens the buy or bid screen for you so the final click stays human.</p>

				<h2>Install</h2>
				<p>
					<a class="btn heat" href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/aimmkefiblmcjppnancgfejmbpcfnddf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
						Add to Chrome
					</a>
				</p>
				<p>Open the popup, click <strong>Sign in to flipagent</strong> to pair, then sign into eBay if you aren't already. Green dot in the popup means it's connected and polling.</p>

				<h2>Score eBay as you browse</h2>
				<p>On any eBay item page or search result, flipagent shows a small chip next to the price. Click it to get an estimated net profit with fees, shipping, and recent sold prices already baked in.</p>
				<p>The side panel opens the deeper view: sold history, active competition, sold price distribution, and a suggested resale band. One credit per listing, cached, so revisiting the same item costs nothing.</p>
				<figure class="docs-figure">
					<img src="/extension/itempage.png" alt="flipagent side panel showing sold history chart, distribution, and price band on a real eBay item page" width="1280" height="800" loading="lazy" />
					<figcaption>The side panel on a live eBay item page.</figcaption>
				</figure>

				<h2>Let your agent buy and bid</h2>
				<p>Your agent calls <code>POST /v1/purchases</code> for a Buy It Now or <code>POST /v1/bids</code> for an auction. The extension opens the right eBay tab, reads the live price, checks it against the cap your agent set, and shows a banner with what to expect.</p>
				<p>You click <strong>Buy It Now</strong> or <strong>Place bid</strong> and confirm. flipagent records the order id (or the bid result) and reports back. The extension never clicks money buttons for you. eBay's User Agreement (effective Feb 20, 2026) requires per-order human review, and that's exactly the line we keep.</p>
				<p>Status flow: <code>queued</code> → <code>processing</code> → <code>completed</code> / <code>failed</code> / <code>cancelled</code>. Poll <code>GET /v1/purchases/&#123;id&#125;</code> until terminal.</p>

				<h2>Permissions and privacy</h2>
				<p>Scoped to <code>ebay.com</code>, <code>app.planetexpress.com</code> (the package forwarder), and the flipagent API. The extension does not read other tabs, does not store your eBay password, and does not persist cookies. After the pair step, only a bridge token (<code>fbt_…</code>) is kept in local storage. Your flipagent API key never leaves your machine.</p>
			</article>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>
